The editorial is a small masterpiece of the deniable: outrage at the violence, support for the investigation, not one sentence that costs the President sleep. Doors open discreetly all autumn — a printing permit, two visas, a professorship. The students read the same editorial and file it where they keep the silences of 1968.

@nombrar
on-arrival: sup_students += 5; represion += 3; expediente += 4; pri_reformist_rel -= 4

The headline asks the question with the four words the entire press corps has been walking around: *¿Quién armó los Halcones?* No answer comes, which is the answer. The issue sells out three printings; the print shop's licenses develop sudden irregularities; and in the university the Party's name is pronounced, for the first time since 1968, without the footnote.
